ns replaced by underscores), you can specify it here.\n\n**Workflow:**\n\n1.  **Initialize:** Run `nbdev_new` in your project's root directory.\n2.  **Provide Information:** Respond to the interactive prompts or use command-line options.\n3.  **Review Configuration:** After `nbdev_new` completes, it's recommended to check the `settings.ini` (or `pyproject.toml` in newer versions) file for accuracy.\n4.  **Build Library:** Run `nbdev_build_lib` to create your Python package from the notebooks.\n5.  **Install Hooks:** It's also common to install Git hooks using `nbdev_install_git_hooks` for a smoother workflow with notebooks.\n\n`nbdev_new` aims to streamline the setup of a new nbdev project by automating as much of the initial configuration as possible."
